s              = {{coord|42|36|15|N|91|32|34|W|region:US-IA|display=inline,title}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|timezone                 = \n|utc_offset               = \n|timezone_DST             = \n|utc_offset_DST           = \n|postal_code_type         = \n|postal_code              = \n|area_code                = \n|blank_name               = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank_info               = [http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:3:::NO::P3_FID:0468602 0468602]\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n}}\n'''Richland Township''' is a [[Civil township|township]] in [[Delaware County, Iowa|Delaware County]], [[Iowa]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 575.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=U.S. Census website |access-date=2008-07-08 }}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nRichland Township covers an area of 36.65 square miles (94.93 square kilometers); of this, 0.18 square miles (0.47 square kilometers) or 0.5 percent is water. The streams of Fenchel Creek and Sand Hagen Creek run through this township.\n\n== History ==\nAccording to the 1870 census, about 883 people lived there. 68 of them were born in [[Bohemia]], several having immigrated from the [[T\u00e1bor District]] from villages like [[Hlavatce (T\u00e1bor District)|Hlavatce]] and [[Val (T\u00e1bor District)|Val]] as well as the town [[Vesel\u00ed nad Lu\u017enic\u00ed]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:MDJB-JGQ|title=United States Census, 1870|last=Simak|first=|date=1870|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://digi.ceskearchivy.cz/DA?menu=3&id=3547&page=34&x=1619&y=1967&z=40|title=DigiArchiv of SRA Trebon - ver. 20.04.17|website=digi.ceskearchivy.cz|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://digi.ceskearchivy.cz/DA?menu=3&id=3487&page=77&x=1490&y=535&z=80|title=DigiArchiv of SRA Trebon - ver. 20.04.17|website=digi.ceskearchivy.cz|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n===Cities and towns===\n* [[Dundee, Iowa|Dundee]]\n\n===Unincorporated towns===\n* [[Forestville, Iowa|Forestville]]\n(This list is based on USGS data and may include former settlements.)\n\n===Adjacent townships===\n* [[Cass Township, Clayton County, Iowa|Cass Township, Clayton County]] (north)\n* [[Lodomillo Township, Clayton County, Iowa|Lodomillo Township, Clayton County]] (northeast)\n* [[Honey Creek Township, Delaware County, Iowa|Honey Creek Township]] (east)\n* [[Delaware Township, Delaware County, Iowa|Delaware Township]] (southeast)\n* [[Coffins Grove Township, Delaware County, Iowa|Coffins Grove Township]] (south)\n* [[Fremont Township, Buchanan County, Iowa|Fremont Township, Buchanan County]] (southwest)\n* [[Madison Township, Buchanan County, Iowa|Madison Township, Buchanan County]] (west)\n* [[Putnam Township, Fayette County, Iowa|Putnam Township, Fayette County]] (northwest)\n\n===Cemeteries===\nThe township contains six cemeteries: Forestville, Pleasant Hill, Reynolds, Saint Albert, Spring Hill and Stanger Farm.\n\n===Major highways===\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121210171316/http://geonames.usgs.gov/domestic/ U.S. Board on Geographic Names (GNIS)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20000815064614/http://www.census.gov/geo/www/cob/ United States Census Bureau cartographic boundary files]\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080905024459/http://www.us-counties.com/localgov/iowa.html US-Counties.com]\n* [http://www.city-data.com/township/Richland-Delaware-IA.html City-Data.com]\n\n{{Delaware County, Iowa}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Townships in Delaware County, Iowa]]\n[[Category:Townships in Iowa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Richland Township\n|settlement_type          = [[Civil township|Township]]\n|nickname                 = \n|mo